<div class=3D"WordSection1">
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hello Raffaella,<o:=
p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Thank you for the e=
mail below.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We can confirm that=
 testing can commence at 2pm on Friday October 17.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We will test from s=
ample sites as required to complete a full and thorough determination of an=
y potential contamination, inclusive of all the areas which you have referr=
ed to below.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">You may undertake y=
our own independent testing at any stage; however, Tower would only conside=
r reimbursement for testing which is - a) claim related &amp; b) testing wh=
ich is outside of that which Tower will
 complete. <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I am confident that=
 the Tower Insurance testing will be transparent, quantified by lab results=
, and adequate to provide comfort for all parties.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Clarified scope =
of testing as follows:<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0in" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 =
lfo1"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">150mm diameter inspection portals cu=
t in wall cavities of every room on the first floor at a height of 300 mm o=
f floor level and directly underneath
 the top plate.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=
=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0p=
t">Testing of the roof cavity at the soffit junction where potential contam=
inants may have risen through the wall cavity. Testing of the roof cavity at
 the apex where smoke may have accumulated.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=
=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><sp=
an style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Testing of the underside of the rear large up=
per deck.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"mar=
gin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Test=
ing of the basement utilizing all exposed framing cavities and 150mm testin=
g portals cut into any remining ceiling linings in the basemen area.<o:p></=
o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso=
-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Any additional sampl=
e sites that we feel are required during testing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></=
o:p></span></li></ul>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><u><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">To ensure effect=
ual testing it would be beneficial if you could confirm the following:<o:p>=
</o:p></span></u></p>
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0in" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l1 level1 =
lfo2"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">That the chlorine was located in the=
 laundry room downstairs at the time of the fire.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li=
 class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo=
2"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">The quantity of the chlorine that was i=
n that room at the time of the fire.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"Mso=
ListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2"><span styl=
e=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Where there any
<u>other chemicals</u> that were located in that same room, or anywhere els=
e downstairs. &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Beyond completing t=
esting and providing laboratory results as described above, I am certain th=
e most productive action we can make towards progressing the claim is to ha=
ve a meeting where we can discuss the
 overall claim response process, providing a forum for you to table any que=
stions, or concerns that you may hold. Those concerns can be responded to, =
and the responses can be documented via minutes with actions and agreements=
 detailed in the minutes providing
 a framework for moving forward with a pre-agreed and productive pathway. I=
 believe this would be very worthwhile and will provide us all with detail,=
 clarity, and documentation that we can all use to our benefit.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Your lawyers and ad=
visors would of course be welcome to attend this meeting.<o:p></o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I look forward to s=
eeing you again on Friday.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Kind Regards,<o:p><=
/o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Grant. &nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"=
><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
